description:
&lt;p&gt;Quality Support Co-ordinator.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;University hospitals Dorset NHS Foundation Trust are looking for an experienced&lt;br /&gt;Quality Coordinator for our Poole site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Purpose of the role&lt;br /&gt;As a Quality support Coordinator, you will be responsible for monitoring and&lt;br /&gt;recording all food safety practices, assessing the quality processes in place to ensure compliance, consistency and continuous improvements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ideally, you will have experience in a similar role. You will hold excellent organisational, communication and administration skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to work in a hot busy environment with a variety of different shift&lt;br /&gt;patterns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your specific responsibilities will include coordinating the following&lt;br /&gt;processes:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;1. Carry out hygiene checks on the standard of food compliance as laid out by the STS folder within the Catering Department, this will be done as often as&lt;br /&gt;required, any non-compliances to be brought to the attention of the Quality&lt;br /&gt;Manager.&lt;br /&gt;2. To be computer literate&lt;br /&gt;3. Carry out waste audits on food trolleys returning from the wards collecting the information &amp; inputting into menu mark, informing the Food Service manager&lt;br /&gt;of any areas of concern.&lt;br /&gt;4. Collect &amp; Record copies of general monitoring.&lt;br /&gt;5. Record Temperatures using the hand held Monica on the belt during both lunch &amp; tea service. Ensure Dining room staff complete theirs&lt;br /&gt;6. Record on STS sheet the temperature of food coming down the belt.&lt;br /&gt;7. Carry out swab tests randomly on areas /equipment in the kitchen &amp; record.&lt;br /&gt;8. Make observations of staff hand hygiene&lt;br /&gt;9. Report where needed to docket line any equipment needing attention or&lt;br /&gt;repairing&lt;br /&gt;10.Issuing/recording of uniforms given&lt;br /&gt;11.Suggesting improvements to Dept. Management and processes to prevent future mistakes during production.&lt;br /&gt;12. To help prepare for external audits.&lt;br /&gt;13. Assist if needed in either Dining Room or Kitchen if necessary&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note: if this job requires you to have a DBS check to enable you to properly fulfil the requirements of the job, on appointment you will be required to repay the cost of obtaining a DBS check and this amount will be reclaimed from your salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 19/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provisional interview date: week commencing 30/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;David Williams, Deputy Catering Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;david.williams3@uhd.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0300 019 2460&lt;/p&gt;
